title: Centrist former Sen. Joseph Lieberman has died at 82
description: As Al Gore's running mate in 2000, Lieberman became the first Jewish candidate on a presidential ticket of one of the two major parties. He later became an independent and was a leader of No Labels.

title: Ronna McDaniel is out. But why are TV networks paying partisan pundits at all?
description: NBC's hiring and firing of former GOP chief Ronna McDaniel may inspire more distrust from conservatives. Yet journalists said her role in trying to overturn the 2020 election made her unacceptable.

title: 8 Tracks: Viral jazz, fantasy metal and a springtime roséwave jam
description: What do New Jazz Underground, Black Sabbath and Remi Wolf have in common? According to NPR Music producer Lars Gotrich, they put out the best tracks of the week.

title: Trump seeks to capitalize on Biden's frustration with Israel's Netanyahu
description: Support for Israel's war in Gaza has fractured along political and religious lines. But Trump's own remarks about Jewish Americans have been sharply criticized.

title: Famed American sculptor Richard Serra, the 'poet of iron,' has died at 85
description: Serra, known for his iconic large-scale pieces of outdoor artwork, died at the age of 85 on Tuesday at his home in Long Island, New York.
